{
  "doc_id": "1312",
  "text": "Pancreatic β-cells require mitochondrial ATP production for glucose-stimulated insulin secretion [CITATION_1] , and are sensitive to defects in mitochondrial function. Thus, many mutations in mitochondrial tRNA genes are associated with diabetes [CITATION_2] , and Kearns-Sayre syndrome, which is due to mtDNA rearrangements, is associated with the development of small pancreatic islets [CITATION_3] and with diabetes [CITATION_4] .",
